4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING THAT CERTAIN PERSONAL PROPERTY IS NOT
5 EXEMPT FROM PROPERTY TAXATION; REVISING THE DEFINITION OF "INTANGIBLE PERSONAL
6 PROPERTY"; AMENDING SECTION 15-6-218, MCA; AND PROVIDING A DELAYED EFFECTIVE DATE AND
7 AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 15-6-218, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "15-6-218. Intangible personal property exemption -- definition. (1) Intangible personal property is
13 exempt from taxation.
14 (2) (a) For the purposes of this section, "intangible personal property" means the following property
15 if it is not integral to the operation of a business or an operating unit of a centrally assessed utility: personal
16 property that is not tangible personal property and that:
17 (a) has no intrinsic value but is the representative or evidence of value, including but not limited to
18 (i) certificates of stock, ;
19 (ii) bonds, ;
20 (iii) promissory notes, ;
21 (iv) licenses, ;
22 (v) copyrights, ;
23 (vi) patents, ;
24 (vii) trademarks, ;
25 (viii) contracts, ;
26 (ix) software, ; and
27 (x) franchises; or
28 (b) lacks physical existence, including but not limited to goodwill.
